atially homogeneous entire positive solution\n$(u^*(t),v^*(t))$. Finally, under some further assumptions, we prove that the\nsystem has a unique entire positive solution $(u^*(x,t),v^*(x,t))$ which is\nglobally stable . Moreover, if $a_i(t,x)$ $(i=0,1,2)$ are periodic or almost\nperiodic in $t$, then $(u^*(x,t),v^*(x,t))$ is also periodic or almost periodic\nin $t$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Sep 2016 05:03:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Oct 2016 03:44:22 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 12 Jan 2017 04:17:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-13"}
